highlights.description: Natalie tells a story about the theft of a coat that was her 9th birthday gift from her parents and what it taught her about the haves and the have nots.
Annalisa talks about her desire as a librarian to pass on some of the love that has been given to her.
Annalisa worries that the thing that makes Harlem so special is slipping away.
Reflections and stories on why people might not feel warm toward their community
Natalie talks about the thing that breaks her about Harlem is a kind of code that says the way to live is to fight and downgrade each other.
Annalisa and Dana talk about the hope that people understand the complexity and history of Harlem
Like Angelina, Natalie experienced living in two worlds that made her sympathetic to the struggles of those in the community living in poverty.
How they see Harlem and define the community.
Another expression about two different worlds living so near one another (rich and poor).
Empathy for folks outside the conversation who have experienced hardships in the community.
Shares personal experience with family addiction in one-sentence go-around.

title: Harlem Launch Conversation - Library staff and community members discuss changes in Harlem
